{"TopicId":179248,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"ModuleManager \u2013 \u2039module-1\u203A OR \u2039module-2\u203A","CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T18:15:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T18:15:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a .cfg file consisting of two conditions with identical bodies:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleCommand]]:Final\n{\n  . . .\n}\n\n@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[KerbalSeat]]:Final\n{\n  . . .\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan I combine them into a single condition?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleCommand]|@MODULE[KerbalSeat]]:Final\n{\n  . . .\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut this didn\u2019t work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-24T18:18:37Z\u0022 title=\u002210/24/2018 06:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Teilnehmer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T20:01:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022143330\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Teilnehmer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Remove the\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E[*]\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0in the second code block. it will help and should work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-25T03:32:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you please explain? As far as I understood, \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003E@NODE[*]\u003C/span\u003E edits all \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003ENODE\u003C/span\u003Es containing a \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003EName\u003C/span\u003E key, but I haven\u2019t found in the documentation what exactly \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003E@NODE\u003C/span\u003E without \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003E[*]\u003C/span\u003E edits. What\u2019s the difference?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-25T16:15:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022143330\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Teilnehmer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Certain nodes, \u0022root nodes\u0022 which have no parent, do not need a \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003E[*]\u003C/span\u003E to be used to target them all. ModuleManager even considers this bad syntax for these, and this is known to break mods that target all science experiment definitions (well, this makes perfect sense as those don\u0027t contain a \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003EName\u003C/span\u003E key).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-25T17:16:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd why should I remove [*] in the second code block only?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-25T17:21:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis should be done with any code block, but I only mentioned the second one as that\u0027s what will allow for your OR condition with the patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-25T17:30:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, I don\u2019t quite get it. What the resulting patch will look like?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}